{
  "id": "jsonbored_metagraphed_1799",
  "repo_name": "jsonbored/metagraphed",
  "repo_url": "https://github.com/jsonbored/metagraphed",
  "base_commit": "4422a9fd188d82d16b05903309c8e6c8461a3ba2",
  "pr_number": 1799,
  "issue_number": 1796,
  "issue_title": "Uptime badge renders 100% for a sub-perfect uptime ratio (scoreFromStats rounds 0.99996 up to 1)",
  "issue_body": "## Summary\n\nThe reliability uptime badge renders `100%` for a subnet whose uptime is not actually perfect (e.g. 99.996%). `scoreFromStats` in `src/reliability.mjs` rounds the displayed `uptime_ratio` to 4 decimals with `Number(uptimeRatio.toFixed(4))`, and `(0.99996).toFixed(4) === \"1.0000\"`, so a sub-1 ratio is stored as an exact `1` before it ever reaches the formatter.\n\n## Why the existing formatter guard does not catch it\n\nThe badge path is:\n\n- `reliabilityContent` -> `loadReliability` (defaults to `loadReliabilityAggregate`, `src/health-serving.mjs:1168`) -> `scoreFromStats` (`src/reliability.mjs:30`) -> returns `uptime_ratio` (line 55)\n- `src/badge.mjs:245`: `formatUptimePercent(rel.uptime_ratio)`\n\n`formatUptimePercent` only demotes a value when `value < 1`. Because `scoreFromStats` has already collapsed `0.99996` to exactly `1`, the `value < 1` guard never fires and the badge prints `100%`. The rounding happens upstream of the formatter, so the information needed to demote is already lost by the time the formatter runs.\n\n## Reproduction\n\n`GET /api/v1/subnets/{netuid}/badge.svg?metric=uptime` for a subnet whose 30-day rollup is `SUM(ok_count)=24999`, `SUM(samples)=25000` (uptime = 99.996%).\n\n- Expected: badge text `99.99%` (sub-perfect uptime must not read as a perfect badge).\n- Actual: badge text `100%`.\n\nThe same applies to the per-surface / per-subnet `uptime_ratio` that `computeReliability` exposes on the live health API: a 99.996% surface reports `uptime_ratio: 1`, overstating it as perfect.\n\n## Expected\n\nOnly a genuine `okCount === samples` (exact `1`) should report `uptime_ratio: 1`. A sub-1 ratio that rounds up to `1` should clamp to the largest 4-decimal value below 1 (`0.9999`), so the badge reads `99.99%` and the health API does not claim a perfect ratio.\n\n## Notes\n\n- `score` / `grade` are unaffected (they are computed from the raw `uptimeRatio`, not the rounded display field).\n- Health is computed live (never from a committed artifact), so the fix does not change any generated `public/` output.\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-06-25T19:24:54.000Z",
